INSERT INTO `config` VALUES (1,'homepage','Home page','<h1>Welcome to the CEAL Statistics Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Council on East Asian Libraries&nbsp;(CEAL) Statistics is an annual publication of statistical data of East Asian libraries and museum collections (volumes held, volumes added gross, current serials, other materials, electronic resources), expenditures (expenditures and grant support), staffing, and services in North America. CEAL annual statistics have been collected and published annually in the Journal of East Asian Libraries (JEAL) since the late 1980s. The online statistics database covers CEAL statistics from 1999 to present with a parallel hard copy publication of CEAL statistics in the February issue of JEAL, the CEAL official publication.&nbsp;Pre 1999 statistics data was added in 2007.&nbsp;The database includes North American East Asian libraries and museums collection statistics published from 1957 to present and contains statistical data from 1869 to present. Quick Views, Simple Search, Advanced Search in Table and Graph displays, PDF, and Log-in Views (collection ranking and peer comparison) have been added for easy access. &nbsp;Collection data can be subdivided by region and funding type. &nbsp;The CEAL collection grand total can be viewed from 1957 to present in addition to collection median and average data. The variety of the statistical data collected is similar to that collected by the <a href=\"https://www.arl.org/\">Association of Research Libraries</a> (ARL) and is included in ARL&#39;s annual statistics. The scope of the CEAL statistics focuses on East Asian libraries and collections and especially Chinese, Japanese, and Korean languages resources, staffing, and service to support East Asian studies in North America.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The database is searchable, with results viewable and printable in table (numbers) and graph formats. Member libraries (with password access) can view library rankings in categories of collection size, expenditures, and grant funding with filters for library type (public or private), and/or geographical region, etc. The database is also serves as a directory of East Asian collections&nbsp;information. The data series is the most comprehensive continuing library statistical dataset among area studies collections in North America. <a href=\"pdfs\">Statistical data published in PDF are available from the web site</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The CEAL Statistics site has been created and maintained by the CEAL Statistics Committee located at the University of Kansas Libraries, Lawrence, KS since 1999.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For new users of this&nbsp;database, please click <a class=\"underline\" href=\"help\" title=\"Contains information for new users to this database\">here</a> for more information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Certain data, such as tables with derived statistical data, can only be accessed by members. Please <a href=\"help\">contact us</a> for information about membership.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Searching the database:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"quick\">Quick View</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Provides a quick view on the statistics of all institutions, containing information about total materials held (including serials).</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"table/basic\">Table View (Basic)</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Search the database with year(s) and libraries, and view all the data and fields available in individual tables.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"table/advanced\">Table View (Advance)</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Search the database with year(s) and libraries, and view the data available in individual tables. Unlike basic view, fields to display can be customized.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"graph/basic\">Graph View (Basic)</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Search the database and view the data available as graphs.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"graph/advanced\">Graph View (Advanced)</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Search the database and view the data available as graphs .Unlike basic view, fields to display can be customized.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"pdfs\">PDF</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;View published data in PDF.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"library/participating\">Participating Libraries</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Contains the list of CEAL participants along with information of CEAL forms submitted, sorted by year.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"library/information\">Library Information</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;View information of CEAL participants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CEAL Statistics by <a href=\"http://www.eastasianlib.org/\" rel=\"cc:attributionURL\">Council on East Asian Libraries </a>Statistics is licensed under a <a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/\" rel=\"license\">Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License</a>.<br />\r\n<strong>Attribution</strong> -&nbsp;You must give&nbsp;<a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/#\" id=\"appropriate_credit_popup\">appropriate credit</a>, provide a link to the license, and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/#\" id=\"indicate_changes_popup\">indicate if changes were made</a>. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.<br />\r\nBased on a work at <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\" rel=\"dct:source\">https://ceal.ku.edu/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h5>The <a href=\"https://ku.edu/\">University of Kansas</a>&#39; <a href=\"https://ceas.ku.edu/\">Center for East Asian Studies</a> Title VI grant has supported the CEAL Statistics Database program upgrades and enhancements since 2005. For 2023, it provided the cost for database server change and enhancement. This vital support keeps the database working for East Asian libraries in North America to gather and disseminate data for not only East Asian collection personnel, but also for scholars, researchers, and grant agencies.</h5>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>','sitetext'),(3,'about','About page','<h1>Council on East Asian Libraries (CEAL) Statistics Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-right col-sm-4 leftpad\">\r\n<p><a href=\"http://asia-www-monitor.blogspot.com/\"><img alt=\"the best of the asian studies banner\" src=\"assets/images/best_of_asian_studies.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">The Asian Studies WWW Monitor: Mar 2008, 15, No. 3 (277)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>The Council on East Asian Library (CEAL) Statistics is an annual publication of statistical data of East Asian libraries and museum collections (volumes held, volumes added gross, current serials, other materials, electronic resources), expenditures (expenditures and grant support), staffing, and services in North America. CEAL annual statistics have been collected and published annually in Journal of East Asian Libraries (JEAL) since late 1980s. The online statistics database covers CEAL statistics from 1999 to present with a parallel hard copy publication of CEAL statistics in the February issue of JEAL, the CEAL official publication. Pre-1999 statistics data was added in 2007. The database includes North America East Asian libraries and museums collection statistics published from 1957 to current which contains statistical data from 1869 to current. Quick Views, Simple Search, Advance Search in Table and Graph displays, PDF, Log-in Views (collection ranking and peer comparison) have been added for easy access. Collection data can be subdivided by region and funding type. CEAL collection grand total can be viewed from 1957 to current in addition to collection median and average data. The variety of statistical data collected is similar to that collected by the Association of Research Libraries (ARL) and is included in ARL&#39;s annual statistics (<a href=\"http://www.arl.org/stats/arlstat/index.html\">http://www.arl.org/stats/arlstat/index.html&quot;</a>). CEAL statistics focus on East Asian collections and especially Chinese, Japanese, and Korean languages resources, staffing, and service to support East Asian studies in North America.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe database is searchable, with results viewable and printable in table (numbers) and graph formats. Member libraries (with password access) can view library rankings in categories of collection size, expenditures, and grant funding with filters of library type (public or private), and/or geographical region, etc. The database is also a directory of East Asian collections contact information, URLs of online catalogs, library system utilities, and more. The data series is the most comprehensive continuing library statistical dataset among area studies collections in North America. Statistical data published in PDF are available from the Committee&#39;s home page (<a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/pdfs\">https://ceal.ku.edu/pdfs</a>).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe CEAL Statistics site has been created and maintained by the CEAL Statistics Committee located at the University of Kansas Libraries, Lawrence, KS since 1999.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Site contents:</strong><br />\r\n* Login; * Quick View; * Table View (Basic); * Table View (Advance); * Graph View; * PDF;<br />\r\n* Participating Libraries (Alberta, Arizona, Arizona State, Art Inst. of Chicago, Binghamton, Brigham Young, British Columbia, Brown, California, Berkeley, California, Davis, California, Irvine, California, Los Angeles, California, Riverside, California, San Diego, California, Santa Barbara, Chicago, Cleveland Museum of Art, Cleveland Public Library, Colorado, Boulder, Columbia, Starr East Asian, Cornell, Dartmouth, Delaware, Duke, Emory University, Far Eastern Research Library, Florida, Georgetown, Harvard Doc. Ctr. on Contemp. Jpn, Harvard-Yenching Library, Hawaii, Illinois-Urbana, Indiana, Inst. for Adv. Studies of World Rel., Iowa, Japan Foundation Toronto, Kansas, Library of Congress, Manitoba, Maryland, McGill, Metropolitan Museum of Art, Michigan, Michigan State, Minnesota, Montreal, Nelson-Atkins Museum of Art, New York Public Library, North Carolina, Oberlin College, Ohio State, Penn State, Pennsylvania, Pittsburgh, Princeton, Queens Borough Public Library, Royal Ontario Museum, Rutgers, Smithsonian Inst. (Freer Gallery), Southern California, Stanford, Texas, Austin, Toronto, Virginia, Washington, Washington, St. Louis, Washington-Law, Wisconsin, Yale.);<br />\r\n* Library Information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>URL</strong>: <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\">https://ceal.ku.edu/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Internet Archive</strong>: <a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/*/www.lib.ku.edu/ceal/\">http://web.archive.org/web/*/www.lib.ku.edu/ceal/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Link reported by</strong>: Vickie Doll/Chair, CEAL Statistics Committee (vdoll--at--ku.edu)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* Resource type [news - documents - study - corporate info. - online guide]: <em>Study</em><br />\r\n* Publisher [academic - business - govt. - library/museum - NGO - other]: <em>Library</em><br />\r\n* Scholarly usefulness [essential - v.useful - useful - interesting - marginal]: <em>Essential</em><br />\r\n* External links to the resource [over 3,000 - under 3,000 - under 1,000 - under 300 - under 100 - under 30]: <em>under 100</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nUpdated in <a href=\"http://coombs.anu.edu.au/asia-www-monitor.html\">The Asian Studies WWW Monitor: Mar 2008, 15, No. 3 (277)</a>, 28 Mar 2008<br />\r\nAs reported in: <a href=\"http://asia-www-monitor.blogspot.com/2005_05_01_archive.html\">The Best of The Asian Studies WWW Monitor, May 2005</a></p>','sitetext'),(4,'help','Help page (new users, cite)','<h1>CEAL Statistics Database Help Page</h1>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-xm-4 pull-right leftpad\">\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\r\n<h3><strong>Contact Information</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For questions or to set up a new user account, please contact:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:anlin.yang@wisc.edu\">Anlin Yang</a><br />\r\nEast Asian Studies Librarian&nbsp;<br />\r\nUniversity of Wisconsin-Madison Libraries</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to Cite</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Council on East Asian Libraries. Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics. in University of Kansas Libraries [database online].<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Lawrence, KS, &copy;2022. Available from <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\">https://ceal.ku.edu/</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>New Libraries</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>New library/institution need to establish an account to join the database. Contact <a href=\"mailto:anlin.yang@wisc.edu\">Anlin Yang</a> to complete a new Library Information Form. The Library Information Form is used as an application to join the CEAL Statistics annual survey.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Change password</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>From CEAL Database:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Log-in to the database as a user</li>\r\n	<li>After you log in to the database, you can change your password immediately by clicking on Change Password link.<br />\r\n	(Tip: &quot;To increase security, please choose a password that does not relate directly to you. Do not use your first name or birthday. Your password is NOT case sensitive. You can use both numeric and character values.&quot;).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>CEAL Statistics Online Forms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You may find complete instruction for online form each year in <a href=\"pdfs\">https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/instructions</a>&nbsp;access under Members tab.<br />\r\nEnter and update your Library Information Form (https://ceal.ku.edu/member/library/)&nbsp; which is under Members tab follow the &quot;My Account&quot; link. This form needs to be filled and updated every year together with all Online Survey Forms. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have further questions regarding online forms and this new version CEAL Stats database, please contact <a href=\"mailto:anlin.yang@wisc.edu\">Anlin Yang</a>.</p>','sitetext'),(5,'pdf_statistics','CEAL Statistics PDFs','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>2022-2023</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2855&amp;context=jeal\">Council on East Asian Libraries Five-Year Statistical Analysis, FY2019&ndash;FY2023: Trends and Insights</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2024: no. 178, Article 6.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2024/iss178/7/\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2022-2023: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2024: no. 178, Article 7.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2024/iss178/8/\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2024&nbsp;: No. 178, Article 8.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2021-2022</strong>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2023/iss176/4\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2021-2022: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2023: no. 176, Article 4.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2023/iss176/5\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2023&nbsp;: No. 176&nbsp;, Article 5.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2020-2021</strong>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2022/iss174/5/\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2020-2021: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2022: no. 174, Article 5.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2022/iss174/6/\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2022&nbsp;: No. 174&nbsp;, Article 6.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2019-2020</strong>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2021/iss172/5/\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2019-2020: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2021: no. 172, Article 5</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2021/iss172/6\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2021&nbsp;: No. 172&nbsp;, Article 6.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2018-2019</strong>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2020/iss170/4/\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2018-2019: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2020: no. 170, Article 4</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2020/iss170/5/\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2020 : No. 170 , Article 5.</p>\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2020/iss170/12/\">2019 CEAL Statistics Summary and Data Analysis</a>,&quot; <em>Journal of East Asian Libraries:</em> Vol. 2020 : No. 170 , Article 12.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2017-2018</strong><p>\r\n	<a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2019/iss168/5/\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2017-2018: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2019: no. 168, Article 5.</p>\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2018/iss166/17\">Lists of Selected Full-text Databases by Subscription in East Asian Studies</a>,&quot;<em> Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>: Vol. 2018 : No. 166 , Article 17.</p>\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2018/iss166/19\">Participating Libraries Organizational Structure and Operation Status, 2017</a>,&quot; <em>Journal of East Asian Libraries:</em> Vol. 2018 : No. 166 , Article 19. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2016-2017</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/vol2018/iss166/16\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2016-2017: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2018: no. 166, Article 16.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2015-2016</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/1808/22713\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2015-2016: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, 2017: no. 164, Article 3.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>2014-2015</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/1808/20316\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2014-2015: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em><em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, </em>no. 162 (February 2016): 41-62.<br />\r\n	<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2013-2014</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"https://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/handle/1808/17117\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2013-2014: For North American Institutions</a>.&nbsp;<em><em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, no. 160 (February 2015): 27-46.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/44\">Instructions for Completing Online Survey Forms</a>&nbsp;Online Forms are available from October 1 through Dec. 12, 2014 (11:59 pm Central Time).<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2012-2013</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/1808/13414\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2012-2013: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, no. 158 (February 2014): 44-67.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2011-2012</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/1808/10956\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2011-2012: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, no. 156 (February 2013): 16-38.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/43\">Instructions for Completing Online Survey Forms</a><br />\r\n	Online Forms are available from October 3 through Dec. 7, 2012 (11:59 pm Central Time).<br />\r\n	<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2010-2011</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10118/1/cealstats2010_11%5B1%5D.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2010-2011: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><em>Journal of East Asian Libraries</em>, no. 154 (February 2012): 53-69.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/42\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	Online Forms are available from September 24 through Dec. 9, 2011 (11:59 pm Central Time).<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2009-2010</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10120/1/cealstats2009_10.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2009-2010: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 152 (February 2011): 42-57.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/41\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2008-2009</strong><br />\r\n	<span class=\"indent\"><a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10152/1/cealstats2008_09.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2008-2009: For North American Institutions</a></span>.<br />\r\n	<em><span class=\"indent\"><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries </i>no.150 (February 2010): 24-43.</span><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/38\">I</a></em><a href=\"download/38\">nstructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2007-2008</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10153/1/cealstat2007_08.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2007-2008: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 147 (February 2009): 50-78.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/40\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2006-2007</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10154/1/cealstat06_07.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2006-2007: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 144 (February 2008): 42-69.<br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/39\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2005-2006</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10155/1/cealstat05_06.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2005-2006: For North American Institutions.</a><br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 141 (February 2007): 51-78.<br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/37\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2004-2005</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10157/1/cealstat04_05.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2004-2005: For North American Institutions.</a><br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 138 (February 2006): 59-85.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/36\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://1.49.209.21/cealemail2005.pdf\">Call for CEAL Statistics 2004/2005 Data Input (E-mail sent to the Eastlib-L, Oct. 10, 2005)</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2003-2004</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10156/1/cealstat03_04.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2003-2004: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 135 (February 2005): 35-62.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/35\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2002-2003</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10158/3/CEALstats_2002_2003.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2002-2003: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 132 (February 2004): 11-35.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/34\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>2001-2002</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"https://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/bitstream/handle/1808/11201/Summary%20of%20CEAL%20Statistics%202001-2002.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics, 2001-2002</a>.<br />\r\n	<i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 129 (Feb, 2003): 77-101.<br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/33\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a> (updated Dec. 4, 2002)<br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/32\">Call for CEAL Statistics 2001-2002 Survey Input (posted on the Eastlib 10/16/2002)</a><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/31\">Questions and Answers on the CEAL Statistics 2001 Online Input Form (PDF)</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>2000-2001</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10160/3/cealstats_2000_2001.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics 2000-2001: For North American Institutions</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 126 (Feb, 2002): 25-52.<br />\r\n	<a href=\"/download/30\">Instructions for Completing Online Forms</a><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>1999-2000</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/45\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics for North American Institutions, 1999-2000.</a><br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries</i>, no. 123 (Feb, 2001): 13-39.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"/download/29\">Instructions for Completing the Questionnaire</a><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/28\">Libraries in the ARL Data Files, 1992-98</a><br />\r\n	http://www.lib.virginia.edu/socsci/arl/1998/institution98.shtml<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>1998-1999</strong><br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/dspace/bitstream/1808/10162/1/CEALstats_1998_1999_revised.pdf\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics for North American Institutions, 1998-1999, Revised</a>.<br />\r\n	<em><i>Journal of East Asian Libraries,</i> no. 122 (October, 2000): 105-121.</em><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/27\">1998-99 Participated Institutions</a><br />\r\n	<a href=\"download/26\">Instructions for Completing the Questionnaire</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span href=\"http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/Dataset\" property=\"dct:title\" rel=\"dct:type\" xmlns:dct=\"http://purl.org/dc/terms/\">CEAL Statistics</span> by <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\" property=\"cc:attributionName\" rel=\"cc:attributionURL\" xmlns:cc=\"http://creativecommons.org/ns#\">Council on East Asian Libraries Statistics</a> is licensed under a <a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/\" rel=\"license\">Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License</a>.<br />\r\n	Based on a work at <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\" rel=\"dct:source\" xmlns:dct=\"http://purl.org/dc/terms/\">lib.ku.edu</a>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"dcont\">\r\n	<p class=\"contact\"><em>Vickie Fu Doll<br />\r\n	vdoll [at sign] ku.edu<br />\r\n	East Asian Library<br />\r\n	University of Kansas,</em></p>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<em> </em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','sitetext'),(7,'login','Login text','<h2>CEAL Statistics Database Login Page</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can login to the CEAL Statistics Database to change information about your institution<strong>. </strong>Every library contact person needs to<strong><mark> use your email as your User ID</mark>, and the Password that you used since your last log-in. If you forget your password, you can request </strong><mark>a<strong> new password by clicking the &quot;<a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/forgotPassword\">Forgot Password&quot; button.</a></strong></mark>&nbsp;<strong>A system assigned password will be sent to individual&#39;s mail box. </strong>CEAL Stats coordinators need to work with their libraries&#39; <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/library/information/\">contact persons</a> to gain access to the database online forms.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','sitetext'),(8,'member_intro','Member page - Intro block (with date)','<h3><strong>CEAL Statistics Database Member Area</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For security purpose, please<strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"../logout\">LOG OFF</a>&nbsp;</strong>or close the browser when you are done.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nInput/Update time frame: <strong><mark>October 1, 2024&nbsp;- December 3, 2024</mark></strong>&nbsp;(11:59:59 pm. Central Time).<br />\r\nStarting from December 4, 2024, the Online Forms won&#39;t be available for input or update by data coordinators.</p>','sitetext'),(9,'survey_instructions','Instructions - Overview (with date)','<h2><strong>Instructions for 2023-2024&nbsp;CEAL Statistics Online Survey</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>2024&nbsp;Online Survey input/edit time frame: <strong><mark>October 1&nbsp;through December 3, 2024&nbsp;(11:59 pm Central Time)</mark></strong><br />\r\n2024&nbsp;CEAL annual statistics will be published in the February 2024&nbsp;online issue of <em>the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/jeal/\">Journal of East Asian Libraries</a></em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u><strong>General Instructions:</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Definitions of the statistical categories used in this questionnaire are based on Information Services and Use: Metrics &amp; Statistics for Libraries and Information Providers &mdash; Data Dictionary&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.niso.org/standards-committees/z397\">NISO Z39.7 (2013)</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>This questionnaire assumes a fiscal year from&nbsp;<strong>July 1, 2023&nbsp;to June 30, 2024</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>Please do not use decimals unless instructed otherwise. All figures should be rounded to the nearest whole number.</li>\r\n	<li>Non-CJK items in this survey refer to non-CJK language materials on East Asia.</li>\r\n	<li>All currencies should be converted to US dollars. Please cooperate with all branch libraries and provide&nbsp;one combined library statistics report for each institution. An exception is given for law libraries. If an appropriate entry is zero or none, use 0.</li>\r\n	<li>Explanatory footnotes will be included with the published statistics. Reporting libraries are urged to record in the footnote section any information that would clarify the figures submitted. <mark><strong>Note: Any large shifts in reported data compared to the previous year should be explained with a footnote.</strong></mark></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><u style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><strong>CEAL Statistics Database (online forms):&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/\">https://ceal.ku.edu</a>&nbsp;[login is required to access forms and instructions]</strong></u></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Log-in. Every institution&nbsp;must follow these&nbsp;instructions to log-in to the CEAL Statistics&nbsp;database.\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>For Institutional Contact Person: if your name has been registered with the system&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/library/information/\">https://ceal.ku.edu/library/information/</a>), you can login with the contact person&#39;s&nbsp;email address as the User ID, and then with the password you obtained since last input. You can also follow the &ldquo;Forgot Password&rdquo; process to setup a new password.</li>\r\n		<li>If you follow the &quot;Forgot Password&quot; process, a&nbsp;system-assigned password will be emailed to you with the subject line: &quot;CEAL Statistics Database&rdquo;. The Statistics Committee members cannot supply you a password. You must follow the process to get the system generated password sent to your email box.</li>\r\n		<li>&shy;All registered CEAL Libraries contact persons need to use his/her email address as the&nbsp;user ID to access your institutional homepage which has the online survey forms and all statistics information about your institution.</li>\r\n		<li>After you enter the database, you can change the password at any time by following the &ldquo;Change Password&rdquo; instructions.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>New member libraries that wish to establish accounts to participate in CEAL annual statistics should contact vdoll[at]ku.edu: See <a href=\"http://&lt;https://ceal.ku.edu/help&quot;&gt;\">instructions for new library</a>.</p>','sitetext'),(11,'latest_year','Latest year to show','2024','setting'),(12,'open_registration','Allow surveys to be submitted for collection year?','2024-10-01','setting'),(13,'current_collection_year','Current collection year','2024','setting'),(14,'personnel_form_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Introductory Paragraph',NULL,'sitetext'),(15,'personnel_form_professional_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Professional Staff Intro','<h3>Professional Staff</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Each library should report those staff members it considers professional, including, when appropriate, staff who are not librarians in the strict sense of the term, for example computer experts, systems analysts, or budget officers.</p>','sitetext'),(16,'personnel_form_support_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Support Staff Intro','<h3>Support Staff</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the total FTE of staff not included in Professional Staff.</p>','sitetext'),(17,'personnel_form_students_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Student Staff Intro','<h3>Student Assistants</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the total FTE of student assistants employed on an hourly basis whose wages are paid from funds under library control&nbsp;<b>or from a budget other</b>&nbsp;than the library&#39;s, including federal work-study programs. Exclude maintenance and custodial staff.</p>','sitetext'),(18,'personnel_form_others_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Other Staff Intro','<h3>Others, FTE:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the number of staff in the parent institution significantly involved in processing and servicing East Asian materials or hired for special projects.</p>','sitetext'),(19,'personnel_form_total_head','Survey - Personnel Support Form - Personnel Total Intro','<h3>Total Personnel</h3>','sitetext'),(20,'close_registration','End survey collection on','2024-12-03','setting'),(22,'complete_instruction_link','Complete Instruction Link','https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/instructions','setting'),(23,'monographicInstructions','Instructions - Monographic Acquisitions','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Monographic Acquisitions Form (Required)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Monographic Titles and Volumes Purchased:</i></b><br />\r\nReport number of titles and volumes purchased.<br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> all titles and volumes for which an expenditure was made during the report year, including titles and volumes paid for in advance but not received during the fiscal year.<br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> monographs in series and continuations.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Purchased Title Chinese<br />\r\n02. Purchased Title Japanese<br />\r\n03. Purchased Title Korean<br />\r\n04. Purchased Title Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>05. Purchased Title Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>06. Purchased Volume Chinese<br />\r\n07. Purchased Volume Japanese<br />\r\n08. Purchased Volume Korean<br />\r\n09. Purchased Volume Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>10. Purchased Volume Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07 + 08 + 09)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Non-Purchased Title Chinese&nbsp;(gifts and&nbsp;exchange)<br />\r\n12. Non-Purchased Title Japanese: (gifts and exchange)<br />\r\n13. Non-Purchased Title Korean: (gifts and exchange)<br />\r\n14. Non-Purchased Title Non-CJK: (gifts and exchange)<br />\r\n<b>15. Non-Purchased Title Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. Non-Purchased Volume Chinese: (Gift volumes and bound periodical volumes)<br />\r\n17. Non-Purchased Volume Japanese: (Gift volumes and bound periodical volumes)<br />\r\n18. Non-Purchased Volume Korean: (Gift volumes and bound periodical volumes)<br />\r\n19. Non-Purchased Volume Non-CJK: (Gift volumes and bound periodical volumes)<br />\r\n<b>20. Non-Purchased Volume Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b>21. Title Total</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(05 + 15)</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>22. Volume Total</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(10 + 20)</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(24,'volumeHoldingInstructions','Instructions - Volume Holdings','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Physical Total Volume Holdings Form (Required)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Previously reported monographs held by the institution will be supplied by the CEAL database</strong>. <u>New libraries</u>&nbsp;need to&nbsp;fill out the data according to individual collections information. Contact vdoll@ku.edu for questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Include</u>:</b> duplicates and bound volumes of periodicals. For purposes of this questionnaire, uncataloged/unclassified bound serials arranged in alphabetical order are considered <span class=\"highlight\">classified</span>.<br />\r\n<b><u>Exclude</u>:</b> microforms, maps, non-print materials, and un-cataloged items.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See the ANSI Z39.7-1995 definition for volume as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Volume</i></b>. <i>A single physical unit of any printed, typewritten, handwritten, mimeographed, or processed work, distinguished from other units by a separate binding, encasement, portfolio, or other clear distinction, which has been cataloged, classified, and made ready for use, and which is typically the unit used to charge circulation transactions. Either a serial volume is bound, or it comprises the serial issues that would be bound together if the library bound all serials</i>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Volumes added:</i></b><br />\r\n<span class=\"highlight\"><b><u>Include</u>:</b> only volumes cataloged, classified, and made ready for use.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:red;\">*The values of fields 01-05 are automatically filled with previous year&#39;s data from CEAL Database (if available). *</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p style=\"color:gray\">01. Previous Chinese*:&nbsp;<br />\r\n02. Previous Japanese*:&nbsp;<br />\r\n03. Previous Korean*:&nbsp;<br />\r\n04. Previous Non-CJK*:<br />\r\n<b>05. Previous Subtotal*</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color:gray\">06. Added Chinese<br />\r\n07. Added Japanese<br />\r\n08. Added Korean<br />\r\n09. Added Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>10. Added Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07 + 08 + 09)</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>11. Withdrawn Chinese<br />\r\n12. Withdrawn Japanese<br />\r\n13. Withdrawn Korean<br />\r\n14. Withdrawn Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>15. Withdrawn Subtotal</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span><br />\r\n<b>16. Grand Total</b>: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(05 + 10 - 15)</span></p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(25,'unprocessedInstructions','Instructions - Unprocessed Backlog Materials','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Unprocessed/Backlog Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report only number of volumes, pieces, etc. that are backlogged.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Include</u>:</b> materials in all formats.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Unprocessed Chinese: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer amount e.g. 70)</span><br />\r\n02. Unprocessed Japanese: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer amount e.g. 70)</span><br />\r\n03. Unprocessed Korean: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer amount e.g. 70)</span><br />\r\n04. Unprocessed Non-CJK: <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer amount e.g. 70)</span><br />\r\n<b>05. Unprocessed Total:</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(26,'serialsInstructions','Instructions - Serial Titles','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Serial Titles:</strong> Purchased and Non-Purchased</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the total number of unique serial titles, purchased and non-purchased. Purchased serial titles are limited to titles with active subscriptions currently being received. Non-purchased serial titles are all other serials held, including previously paid-for serials that have ceased or no longer have current subscriptions.&nbsp;<b>Do not include</b> duplicate counts of serial titles. To the extent possible, report all government document serials even if housed in a separate document collection. Verify the inclusion or exclusion of document serials. Exclude unnumbered monographic and publishers&#39; series. Electronic serials acquired as part of a bundle or an aggregated package should be counted by title, even if they are not cataloged, as long as they are made accessible by the library.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See the ANSI Z39.7-1995 definition for serial as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Serial</i></b>. <i>A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended to be continued indefinitely. This definition includes periodicals, newspapers, and annuals (reports, yearbooks, etc.); the journals, memoirs, proceedings, transactions, etc. of societies; and <span style=\"color:#990000\">numbered monographic series.</span></i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Serial Titles (electronic) Currently Purchased (include electronic subscription)</i></b><br />\r\nIn the case of consortial agreements, count those titles for which the library pays any amount from its budgeted expenditures under &#39;serial titles currently purchased&#39;. Include all titles that are part of bundles or aggregated packages, even if your library makes a partial payment for access to those titles. If a database includes full-text and abstracted titles, the number of full-text titles can be counted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">&quot;<em>Import from&nbsp;E-Journal Database by Subscription</em>&quot;</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><mark>BEFORE using the import feature, please fill out or update&nbsp;the &quot;</mark></strong><em><strong><mark><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/ejournal/edit\">E-Journals Database by Subscription &ndash; List of</a></mark></strong></em><strong><mark>&quot; in order for the system to provide the corresponding numbers automatically.&nbsp;</mark></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If separate counts of non-purchased and purchased serials are not available, report only the total number (titles) of current subscribed&nbsp;serials on line 15, and others &quot;0&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.1 Purchased Serials (includes Subscriptions) - Electronic</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Purchased Chinese (Electronic)<br />\r\n02. Purchased Japanese (Electronic) [ex.&nbsp;太陽, 美術新報 via JapanKnowledge]<br />\r\n03. Purchased Korean (Electronic)<br />\r\n04. Purchased Non-CJK (Electronic)<br />\r\n<b>05. Purchased Total (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span class=\"sumtxt\">1.2 Purchased Serials (includes Subscriptions) - Prints and other formats&nbsp;</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>06. Purchased Chinese (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n07. Purchased Japanese (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n08. Purchased Korean (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n09. Purchased Non-CJK (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n<b>10. Purchased Total (Print and other formats)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>2.1 Non-Purchased Serials (includes Gifts) - Electronic &nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Non-Purchased Chinese (Electronic)<br />\r\n12. Non-Purchased Japanese (Electronic)<br />\r\n13. Non-Purchased Korean (Electronic)<br />\r\n14. Non-Purchased Non-CJK (Electronic)<br />\r\n<b>15. Non-Purchased Total (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<h3><strong>2.2 Non-Purchased Serials (includes Gifts) - Prints and other formats</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>16. Non-Purchased Chinese (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n17. Non-Purchased Japanese (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n18. Non-Purchased Korean (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n19. Non-Purchased Non-CJK (Print and other formats)<br />\r\n<b>20. Non-Purchased Total (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>3.1 Totals - Electronic Serials</b></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>21. Total Chinese (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 11)</span><br />\r\n<b>22. Total Japanese (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(02 + 12)</span><br />\r\n<b>23. Total Korean (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(03 + 13)</span><br />\r\n<b>24. Total Non-CJK (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(04 + 14)</span><br />\r\n<b>25. Grand Total (Electronic)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(05 + 15)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span class=\"sumtxt\">3.2 Totals - Prints and other formats&nbsp;</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><b>26. Total Chinese (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 16)</span><br />\r\n<b>27. Total Japanese (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(07 + 17)</span><br />\r\n<b>28. Total Korean (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(08 + 18)</span><br />\r\n<b>29. Total Non-CJK (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(09 + 19)</span><br />\r\n<b>30. Grand Total (Print and other formats)</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(10 + 20)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span class=\"sumtxt\">3.3 Grand Totals</span></strong></h3>','sitetext'),(27,'publicServicesInstructions','Instructions - Public Services','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Public Services</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Presentations:</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Number of Library Presentations:</i></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Presentations to Groups</i></b><br />\r\nReport the total number of sessions of class presentations, orientation sessions, tours, and bibliographic instruction for the year.&nbsp;Presentations may be for cultural, recreational, or educational purposes. If the library sponsors multi-session or credit courses that meet several times over the course of a semester, each session should be counted. Presentations both on and off the premises should be included as long as they are sponsored by the library. Do not include meetings sponsored by other groups using library meeting rooms. Do not include training for library staff. Sampling and/or estimation is acceptable; please indicate if figure is based on sampling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Participants in Group Presentations</i></b><br />\r\nReport the total number of participants in the presentations. For multi-session classes with a constant enrollment, count each person only once. Personal, one-to-one instruction in the use of sources should be counted as reference transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Library Presentations <span style=\"color:navy;\">(Number of presentations)</span><br />\r\n02. Participants <span style=\"color:navy;\">(Number of participants in presentations)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Reference Transactions:</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nReport the total number of reference transactions. <strong>A reference transaction is an information contact and involves the knowledge, recommendation, interpretation, or instruction in the use of information sources by a member of the library staff</strong>. The term includes information and referral service. Information sources include (a) printed and non-printed material; (b) machine-readable databases (including computer-assisted instruction); (c) the library&#39;s own catalogs and records of other holdings; (d) other libraries and institutions through communication or referral; and (e) persons both inside and outside the library. When a staff member answers a question by using information gained from previous use of information sources, the transaction is still reported as a reference transaction even though the source was not consulted at that time.<br />\r\nIf a contact includes both reference and directional services, it should be reported as one reference transaction. Include virtual reference transactions (e.g., e-mail, WWW form, chat). Duration should not be an element in determining whether a transaction is a reference transaction. Please indicate if the figure is based on sampling. (see&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ala.org/rusa/resources/guidelines/definitionsreference\">ARL Reference Transaction</a>;<a href=\"http://z39-7.niso.org/standard/section7.html\"> ANSI/NISO Z39.7-2013, Information Services and Use: Metrics &amp; Statistics for Libraries and Information Providers</a>&nbsp;&ndash; Data Dictionary)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the total number of reference transactions handled in person, online, or over the telephone.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>03. Reference Transactions</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><em><b>Total Circulation:</b></em></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nCount the number of<strong> initial circulations</strong> (excluding reserves) for the general collection during the fiscal year. Do not count renewals. Exclude e-books. Include circulations to and from remote storage facilities for library users (i.e. do not include transactions reflecting transfers or stages of technical processing). <u>Count the total number of items lent, not the number of borrowers.</u></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>04. Total Circulations</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Interlibrary Loans:</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the number of requests for other libraries&#39; or providers&#39; material (both returnables and non-returnables) and the number of filled requests received. Include originals, photocopies, and materials sent by telefacsimile or other forms of electronic transmission. Include patron-initiated transactions. Exclude requests for materials locally owned and available on shelves or electronically. Do not include transactions&nbsp;<em>between</em>&nbsp;the main libraries&nbsp;and branches&nbsp;within the same institution/university.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the numbers of filled and unfilled requests provided to and received from other libraries. When appropriate, include document delivery statistics.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>05. Lending Request Filled<br />\r\n06. Lending Request Unfilled<br />\r\n07. Borrowing Request Filled<br />\r\n08. Borrowing Request Unfilled</p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(28,'personnelInstructions','Instructions - Personnel Support','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Personnel Support Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the number of FTE (full-time equivalent) staff in filled positions and positions that are only temporarily vacant.<br />\r\nFor employees working for more than one language, estimate percentiles worked under each CJK language or report as East Asian.. Report in decimals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Professional Staff</i></b><br />\r\nEach library should report staff members it considers professional.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Professional Chinese <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer or decimal)</span><br />\r\n02. Professional Japanese <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer or decimal)</span><br />\r\n03. Professional Korean <span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer or decimal)</span><br />\r\n04. Professional East Asian&nbsp;<span class=\"sumtxt\">(integer or decimal)</span><br />\r\n05. Professional Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Support Staff</i></b><br />\r\nReport the total FTE of staff not included in Professional Staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>06. Support Chinese<br />\r\n07. Support Japanese<br />\r\n08. Support Korean<br />\r\n09. Support East Asian<br />\r\n10. Support Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07 + 08 + 09)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Student Assistants</i></b><br />\r\nReport the total FTE of student assistants employed on an hourly basis whose wages are paid from funds under library control <b>or from a budget other</b> than the library&#39;s, including federal work-study programs. Exclude maintenance and custodial staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">11. Student Chinese<br />\r\n12. Student Japanese<br />\r\n13. Student Korean<br />\r\n14. Student East Asian<br />\r\n15. Student Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 +13 +14)</span></div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Others, FTE:</i></b><br />\r\nReport the number of staff in the parent institution significantly involved in processing and servicing East Asian materials or hired for special projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>16. Other</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b>17. Total Personnel</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(05 + 10 + 15 + 16)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span class=\"sumtxt\"><font color=\"#00000018\">18. Select&nbsp;Yes or No for outsourced acquisition in the survey year.&nbsp;</font></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>19. Select Yes or No for outsourced processing in the survey year.</b></p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(29,'otherInstructions','Instructions - Other Materials','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Holdings of Other Materials Form (Required)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"red\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">This is a count for the entire library&#39;s accumulated, up-to-date, TOTAL holdings of &quot;other materials.&quot;&nbsp; Online subscription accessible items do not count toward the grand total libray holdings.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"red\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Please DO NOT&nbsp;report only those new acquisitions for the survey year.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"red\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Report individual piece count, not a collective title count.<br />\r\nFor example: if there are several DVDs&nbsp;under one title, list the DVD number count.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Microforms</b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report the <u><strong>GRAND TOTAL</strong></u>&nbsp;number of physical units: reels of microfilm, microcards, microprint, and microfiche sheets.<br />\r\n<u>Include</u> all government documents in microform; provide a footnote if documents are excluded.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Microform Chinese<br />\r\n02. Microform Japanese<br />\r\n03. Microform Korean<br />\r\n04. Microform Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>05. Microform Subtotal</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Cartographic and Graphic Materials</b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Include</u>:</b> number of two- and three- dimensional maps and globes<br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> number of satellite and aerial photographs and images<br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> number of prints, pictures, photographs, postcards, slides, transparencies, film strips, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>06. Graphic Chinese<br />\r\n07. Graphic Japanese<br />\r\n08. Graphic Korean<br />\r\n09. Graphic Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>10. Graphic Subtotal</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07+ 08 + 09)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Audio, Film, and Video Materials</b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Include</u>:</b> number of audiocassettes, phonodiscs, audio compact discs, reel-to-reel tapes, and other sound recordings<br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> number of motion pictures, videocassettes, video laser discs, and similar visual materials</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>11. Audio Chinese<br />\r\n12. Audio Japanese<br />\r\n13. Audio Korean<br />\r\n14. Audio Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>15. Audio Subtotal</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>16. Video Chinese<br />\r\n17. Video Japanese<br />\r\n18. Video Korean<br />\r\n19. Video Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>20. Video Subtotal</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>21. DVD Chinese<br />\r\n22. DVD Japanese<br />\r\n23. DVD Korean<br />\r\n24. DVD Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>25. DVD Subtotal:</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(21 + 22 + 23 + 24)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"red\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">For Online Materials Below:&nbsp;</span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">&quot;<em>Import from&nbsp;Audio-Visual Database by Subscription</em>&quot;</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><mark>BEFORE using the import feature, please fill out or update&nbsp;the &quot;<em><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/av/edit\">Audio-Visual Database by Subscription - List of</a>&nbsp;</em>&quot; in order for the system to provide the corresponding numbers automatically.&nbsp;</mark></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong><strong><strong>Online Map</strong></strong></strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>26. Online Map Chinese<br />\r\n27. Online Map Japanese<br />\r\n28. Online Map Korean<br />\r\n29. Online Map Non-CJK<br />\r\n<strong>30. Online Map Subtotal :&nbsp;</strong>(<span class=\"sumtxt\">26 + 27 + 28 + 29)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong><strong>Online Image/Photograph<strong><font color=\"red\">&nbsp;</font></strong></strong></strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>31. Online Image/Photograph Chinese<br />\r\n32. Online Image/Photograph Japanese<br />\r\n33. Online Image/Photograph Korean<br />\r\n34. Online Image/Photograph Non-CJK<br />\r\n<strong>35. Online Image/Photograph Subtotal : </strong>(<span class=\"sumtxt\">31 + 32 + 33 + 34)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong><strong><strong>Streaming Audio/Music</strong></strong></strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>36. Streaming Chinese<br />\r\n37. Streaming Japanese<br />\r\n38. Streaming Korean<br />\r\n39. Streaming Non-CJK<br />\r\n<strong>40. Streaming Video/Film Subtotal :</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"sumtxt\">(36 + 37 + 38 + 39</span>)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong><strong><strong>Streaming Film/Video&nbsp;</strong></strong></strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>41. Streaming Chinese<br />\r\n42. Streaming Japanese<br />\r\n43. Streaming Korean<br />\r\n44. Streaming Non-CJK<br />\r\n<strong>45. Streaming Video/Film Subtotal&nbsp;</strong>(<span class=\"sumtxt\">41 + 42 + 43 + 44)</span> &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><mark>Libraries that need to report material types other than those provided above should contact vdoll@ku.edu&nbsp;for assistance.</mark></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Custom&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong>46 - 49. Custom field (description)</strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>Chinese<br />\r\nJapanese<br />\r\nKorean<br />\r\nNon-CJK<br />\r\nSubtotal</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong>50. Custom Subtotals</strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><label for=\"cealbundle_otherholdings_ohgrandtotal\">51. Other Holdings Total&nbsp;</label></strong>(05 + 10 + 15 + 20 + 25)</strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Notes:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><label for=\"cealbundle_otherholdings_ohnotes\">52. Memo/Footnote for this form</label></strong></strong></strong></strong></p>','sitetext'),(30,'fiscalInstructions','Instructions - Fiscal Support','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Fiscal Support Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><b><font size=\"+1\">This is the only form which accepts subtotals and totals filled manually without filling breakdown cells.&nbsp;</font></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Appropriations section allows manual input to subtotals cells 5, 10, 15, and 20 without input to breakdown cells.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also fill the Total Appropriations cell 21 and leave cells 1-20 blank.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><font size=\"+1\"><mark><b>A forced grand total or subtotal must be filled manually.</b></mark>&nbsp;</font></p>\r\n\r\n<p><font size=\"+1\"><mark><b>Cell&nbsp;#37 <u>Total Acquisitions Budget</u>&nbsp;must be filled manually.</b></mark></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Report all currency in U.S. Dollars&nbsp;(<a href=\"http://www.bank-banque-canada.ca/en/exchform.htm\">Currency Converter</a>).&nbsp;Convert Canadian currency to U.S. dollars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Note: <font color=\"red\"><u>Do not</u> use dollar signs or &quot;thousands separator&quot; commas</font></b><font color=\"red\"><b>, e.g. input 50600 instead of $50,600.</b></font>&nbsp;Please round figures to the nearest dollar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Report all funds that come to the library from the regular institutional budget and from sources such as research grants, endowments, and East Asian programs support for acquisition of library materials.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Appropriations</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report funds from the library for monographs, serials, and other materials for CJK and non-CJK languages. If figures for specific language areas are not available, only report the total.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Chinese Appropriations Monographic<br />\r\n02. Chinese Appropriations Serial<br />\r\n03. Chinese Appropriations Other Materials<br />\r\n04. Chinese Appropriations Electronic Resources<br />\r\n<b>05. Chinese Appropriations Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 +04)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>06. Japanese Appropriations Monographic<br />\r\n07. Japanese Appropriations Serial<br />\r\n08. Japanese Appropriations Other Materials<br />\r\n09. Japanese Appropriations Electronic Resources<br />\r\n<b>10. Japanese Appropriations Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07 + 08 +09)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>11. Korean Appropriations Monographic<br />\r\n12. Korean Appropriations Serial<br />\r\n13. Korean Appropriations Other Materials<br />\r\n14. Korean Appropriations Electronic Resources<br />\r\n<b>15. Korean Appropriations Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. Non-CJK Appropriations Monographic<br />\r\n17. Non-CJK Appropriations Serial<br />\r\n18. Non-CJK Appropriations Other Materials<br />\r\n19. Non-CJK Appropriations Electronic Resources<br />\r\n<b>20. Non-CJK Appropriations Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b>21. Total Appropriations</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(05 + 10 + 15 + 20)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Endowments</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report funds from endowments. If figures for specific area studies are not available, only report the total.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>22. Endowments Chinese<br />\r\n23. Endowments Japanese<br />\r\n24. Endowments Korean<br />\r\n25. Endowments Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>26. Endowments Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(22 + 23 + 24 + 25)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>Grants</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report funds from grants. If figures for specific area studies are not available, only report the total.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">27. Grants Chinese<br />\r\n28. Grants Japanese<br />\r\n29. Grants Korean<br />\r\n30. Grants Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>31. Grants Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(27 + 28 + 29 + 30 )</span></div>\r\n\r\n<h4><b><i>East Asian Program Support</i></b></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Report funds from East Asian program. If figures for specific area studies are not available, only report the total.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">32. East Asian Program Support Chinese<br />\r\n33. East Asian Program Support Japanese<br />\r\n34. East Asian Program Support Korean<br />\r\n35. East Asian Program Support Non-CJK<br />\r\n<b>36. East Asian Program Support Total</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(32&nbsp;+ 33&nbsp;+ 34 + 35)</span>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>37. Total Acquisitions Budget</b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(21 + 26&nbsp;+ 31&nbsp;+ 36)</span></h4>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><mark><b>Fill in the cell 37 Total Acquisitions Budget manually!&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></mark><strong>The system does NOT supply the grand total and subtotals if those are forced filled data with blank breakdown cells.</strong></p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(31,'electronicBookInstructions','Instructions - Electronic Books','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Electronic Books Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"underline\">Report the number of electronic books held.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><u>Include</u>&nbsp;e-book units, as long as these e-books <strong>are owned or leased</strong> <strong>and have been cataloged by your library. (both groups #01-04 and #06-09 in title ADDED;&nbsp;both groups #16-19 and&nbsp;#21-24 in volume&nbsp;ADDED)</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><u>Include</u> electronic books purchased through vendors such as EBSCO&reg;,&nbsp;ProQuest, Taylor and Francis,&nbsp;Brill, etc.; and Chinese, Japanese, and Korean e-book vendors, and e-books that come as part of aggregate services. <strong>(#01-04 titles and&nbsp;#16-19 volumes ADDED&nbsp;</strong>)&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><u>Include</u> locally digitized electronic books and electronic theses and dissertations <strong>(#06-09 titles and #21-24 volume&nbsp;ADDED)</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><u><strong>Exclude</strong> </u>any item from HathiTrust, CRL, CADAL, and Internet Archive, etc. <u>unless</u> it meets the above conditions<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Purchased Titles</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01.<strong> Purchased </strong>E-Books Title&nbsp;Chinese<span style=\"font-size:80%; color:red;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>[Number of titles from last year is supplied by the&nbsp;system]</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year [ex. Airiti, Apabi, ChinaMaxx, East View, Airiti&nbsp;ebooks, and etc.]</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles total this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>02. <strong>Purchased</strong> E-Books Title&nbsp;Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>[Number of titles from last year is supplied by the&nbsp;system]</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles total this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>03. <strong>Purchased</strong> E-Books Title&nbsp;Korean<span style=\"font-size:80%; color:red;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>[Number of titles from last year is supplied by the&nbsp;system]</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles total this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>04. <strong>Purchased</strong> E-Books Title NonCJK <span style=\"font-size:80%; color:red;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>[Number of titles from last year is supplied by the&nbsp;system]</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year</li>\r\n	<li>Number of titles total this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>05. Subtotal Purchased/ADDED E-Books Title </strong>(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Non-Purchased Titles</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>06. Non-Purchased E-Books Title Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>07. Non-Purchased E-Books Title Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>08. Non-Purchased E-Books Title Korean</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>09. Non-Purchased E-Books Title Non-CJK</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Number of titles ADDED this year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>10. Subtotal Non-Purchased E-Books Title&nbsp;</strong>(06 + 07 + 08 +09)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Subscription Titles (Accessed by subscription, both purchased and by subscription only)&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">&quot;<em>Import from&nbsp;E-book Database by Subscription</em>&quot;</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><mark>BEFORE using the import feature, please fill out or update&nbsp;the &quot;<em><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/ebook/edit\">E-Book Database by Subscription &ndash; List of</a></em>&quot; in order for the system to provide the corresponding numbers automatically.&nbsp;</mark></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>11.<strong> Subscription</strong> E-Books Title Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. <strong>Subscription</strong> E-Books Title Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. <strong>Subscription </strong>E-Books Title Korean</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14.<strong> Subscription</strong> E-Books Title NonCJK</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>15. Subtotal Subscription E-Books Title</b> (11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Purchased Volumes</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>16. Purchased E-Books Volume Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>17. Purchased E-Books Volume Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>18. Purchased E-Books Volume Korean</p>\r\n\r\n<p>19. Purchased E-Books Volume NonCJK</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>20. Subtotal Purchased E-Books Volume</b>&nbsp;(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Non-Purchased Volumes</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>21 Non-Purchased E-Books Volume Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>22.&nbsp;Non-Purchased E-Books Volume Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>23.&nbsp;Non-Purchased E-Books Volume Korean</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24.&nbsp;Non-Purchased E-Books Volume&nbsp; Non-CJK</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>25. Subtotal Non-Purchased E-Books Volume </strong>(21 + 22 + 23 + 24)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"subscriptionVolumes\">Subscription Volumes</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&quot;<em>Import from&nbsp;E-book Database by Subscription</em>&quot;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><mark>BEFORE using the import feature, please fill out or update&nbsp;the &quot;<em><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/ebook/edit\">E-Book Database by Subscription &ndash; List of</a></em>&quot; in order for the system to provide the corresponding numbers automatically.&nbsp;</mark></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>26. Subscription E-Books Volume Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>27. Subscription E-Books Volume Japanese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>28. Subscription E-Books Volume Korean</p>\r\n\r\n<p>29. Subscription E-Books Volume NonCJK</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>30. Subtotal Subscription E-Books Volume </b>&nbsp;(26 + 27 + 28 + 29)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Totals</h4>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b>31. Total E-Books Title&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>32. Total E-Books Volume</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b>33. Total E-Books Expenditure</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"redtxt fntBold fnt090\">Note: Form 9&nbsp;Electronic Resources: Grand Total Expenditures (cell 41) includes expenditures for Electronic Books. Please enter data there if you have not done so.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>34. Memo/Footnote for this form</p>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(32,'electronicInstructions','Instructions - Electronic Resources','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Electronic Resources Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Questions 1 and 2 are intended to gather a complete picture of electronic resources in a collection. <strong>Question 2 should reflect&nbsp;a count of databases</strong> (not a count of eJournal or eBook titles&nbsp;within databases) for the library&#39;s entire database&nbsp;collection in the survey year. For each question, use the following general inclusion and exclusion guidelines:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Include</u>:</b> paid subscriptions or one-time purchases of electronic indexes and reference tools, electronic full-text periodical collections and electronic journal back-files, online searches of remote databases -- whether accessed remotely or installed locally from CD-ROM, magnetic tapes, magnetic disks, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Also include</u>:</b> materials purchased jointly with other institutions if such expenditures can be separated from other charges for joint services, fees paid to bibliographic utilities if the portion paid for computer files and search services can be counted separately, and equipment costs when they are bundled together into the price of the information product. <b><span style=\"color:#990000;\">A count of total expenditures on electronic resources for the statistical year is required in this form.</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Exclude</u>:</b> bibliographic utilities, networks, and consortia that are unrelated to end-user database access<span style=\"color:blue;\">. </span>Also exclude system software and software used only by the library staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:110%; font-weight:bold;\">1. COMPUTER FILES</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span><b><u>Include</u>:</b> the survey year received number of pieces of computer-readable disks, tapes, CD-ROMs, and similar machine-readable files comprising data or programs that are <b>locally held as part of the library&#39;s collections</b> available to library clients. Examples: U.S. Census data tapes, sample research software, locally-mounted databases, and reference tools on CD-ROM, tape, or disk.<br />\r\n<b><u>Exclude</u>:</b> bibliographic records used to manage the collection (i.e., the library&#39;s own catalog in machine-readable form), library system software, and microcomputer software used only by the library staff.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>1.1 Computer Files (one-time/monographic purchase)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>01. Number of Chinese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n02. Number of Japanese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n03. Number of Korean Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n04. Number of Non-CJK Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n<b>05. Subtotal</b> Number of Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 02 + 03 + 04)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b><i>Comments for 1.1</i></b><br />\r\nReport the survey year received numbers of titles and expenditures of computer files that are not current serials (i.e. are non-subscription, one-time, or monographic in nature) for software or machine-readable materials considered part of the collections.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples: periodical backfiles, literature collections such as Er shi wu shi (<font size=\"-1\">二十五史</font>, by Jinan Huiwei), Si ku quan shu (<font size=\"-1\">四庫全書</font>, CD-ROM), Zhongguo bai ke da ci dian (<font size=\"-1\">中国百科大辞典</font>), Zhonghua bo shuo shi lun wen jian suo guang die (Chinese Dissertation Reference CD, <font size=\"-1\">中華博碩士論文檢索光碟</font>), Genji monogatari honbun kenkyū dētabēsu, Kugyok Choson wangjo sillok = Annals of the Chosun dynasty, Hanguk hyondae munhak 100-yon = Korean modern literature 100 years, Koryo taejanggyong (<font size=\"-1\">高麗大藏經</font>).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>1.2 Computer Files (Accompanying monographic purchase or serials subscription)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>06. Number of Chinese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n07. Number of Japanese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n08. Number of Korean Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n09. Number of Non-CJK Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n<b>10. Subtotal</b> Number of Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(06 + 07 + 08 + 09)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b><i>Comments for 1.2</i></b><br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> CD-ROMs that accompany a primary format such as printed serials subscriptions and monographic purchases. Examples include CDs that come with the Japanese government&#39;s annual hakusho (<font size=\"-1\">白書</font>), Chinese yearbook (<font size=\"-1\">年鉴</font>), and Korean periodical Shin Donga (<font size=\"-1\">新東亞</font>). These expenditures have already been included in either monographic or serials subscriptions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>1.3 Computer Files (One time gift items that come either alone or accompanying a printed gift)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>11. Number of Chinese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n12. Number of Japanese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n13. Number of Korean Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n14. Number of Non-CJK Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n<b>15. Subtotal</b> Number of Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(11 + 12 + 13 + 14)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b><i>Comments for 1.3</i></b><br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b> gift items that were not included in subscriptions in 1.1 nor 1.2.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>1.4 Total Computer Files (1.1 + 1.2 + 1.3)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>16. Number of&nbsp;Chinese&nbsp;Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(01 + 06 + 11)</span><br />\r\n17.&nbsp;Number of Japanese&nbsp;Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(02 + 07 + 12)</span><br />\r\n18. Number of&nbsp;Korean Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(03 + 08 + 13)</span><br />\r\n19. Number of Non-CJK&nbsp;Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(04 + 09 + 14)</span><br />\r\n<b>20. Total</b> Number of Titles and CD-ROMs <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 17 + 18 + 19)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b>1.5 Previous Total Computer Files</b><br />\r\n(System supplied data from previous years)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>21. Number of Chinese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n22. Number of Japanese Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n23. Number of Korean Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n24. Number of Non-CJK Titles and CD-ROMs<br />\r\n<b>25. <b>TOTAL (of previous years)</b>&nbsp;: Number of Titles and discs</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b>1.5.1 Grand Total Computer Files</b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b><b><u>Note</u>:</b> </b>21.1 to 25.1 are grayed out. Data will be calculated automatically after the submission.<br />\r\n(Grand Total = Previous Year + Current Year).<br />\r\n<b><b>New libraries and libraries that do not have the &quot;previous year&quot; figures will be able to fill in figures on the current year survey.</b></b></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>21.1. Chinese <span class=\"sumtxt\">(16 + 21)</span><br />\r\n22.1. Japanese <span class=\"sumtxt\">(17 + 22)</span><br />\r\n23.1. Korean <span class=\"sumtxt\">(18 + 23)</span><br />\r\n24.1. Non-CJK <span class=\"sumtxt\">(19 + 24)</span><br />\r\n25.1. Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(21.1 + 22.1 + 23.1 + 24.1)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b><span style=\"font-size:110%;\">2. ELECTRONIC DATABASES (remote access on-going/leases/subscriptions)</span></b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b><span style=\"color:red;\">Note: The majority of electronic resources (2.1-2.2) via online access are considered to be subscriptions.&nbsp;</span></b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Report the number of titles and subscription expenditures (and those which are expected to be ongoing commitments) for serial publications where the primary format is electronic; also report the number of remote databases. Count each subject module separately as each has its&nbsp;content cost.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b><u>Exclude</u>:</b> </b>print serials that are accompanied by CD-ROMs (use 1.2).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b><u>Include</u>:</b></b> paid subscriptions for electronic journals and indexes/abstracts available via the Internet with annual access fees purchased on a &quot;one-time&quot; basis. See 2.1 and 2.2 for details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.1 <mark><u><u>Indexes</u>, bibliographies,&nbsp;references, and non full-text</u></mark></strong>&nbsp;<strong>electronic databases</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>26. Number of Chinese Langauge Databases<br />\r\n27. Number of Japanese Language Databases&nbsp;<br />\r\n28. Number of Korean Language Databases<br />\r\n29. Number of Non-CJK Databases<br />\r\n30. Subtotal Number of Databases <span class=\"sumtxt\">(26 + 27 + 28 + 29)</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b><b><i>Comments for 2.1</i></b><br />\r\n<b><u>Include</u>:</b></b> paid subscriptions or one-time purchases of reference tools such as encyclopedias, almanacs, indexes, and abstracts.<br />\r\nExamples: Bibliography of Asian Studies, Digital dictionary of Buddhism, Quan guo bao kan zi liao suo yin (全国报刊资料索引),&nbsp;Toyo Keizai Digital Content Library, Zasshi kiji sakuin shūsei dētabēsu [electronic resource] : Meiji kara genzai made sōgō zasshi (雑誌記事索引集成データベース), MagazinePlus, Nichigai/web sābisu (BookPlus, Magazineplus, WhoPlus), Tonga inmul chŏngbo 동아인물정보, EncyKorea, etc.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b><b><u>Exclude</u>:</b> </b>expenditures for indexes and abstracts which include substantial access to ASCII text or full images of serial content, which should be reported in 2.2. In 2.1, the primary content is abstract or index in nature.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b>2.2 <u>Full-text full-content</u>&nbsp;electronic databases&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></b><br />\r\n<b><b><mark>(includes full-text E-Book, E-Journal, and Audio-Visual&nbsp;databases)</mark></b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:red;background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">&quot;<em>Import from&nbsp;E-Book,&nbsp;E-Journal, and Audio-Visual Databases</em>&quot;</span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><mark>BEFORE using the import feature, please fill out or update&nbsp;the <em><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/ebook/edit\">E-book</a></em>,&nbsp;</mark></strong><em><strong><mark><a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/ejournal/edit\">E-Journal</a>, <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/av/edit\">Audio-Visual</a> lists </mark></strong></em><strong><mark>in order for the system to provide the corresponding numbers automatically.&nbsp;</mark></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><mark>These lists are also listed at the end&nbsp;at the <a href=\"https://ceal.ku.edu/member/forms/survey/forms/edit\">Online Form front page</a>.</mark></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>31. Number of Chinese databases&nbsp;<span class=\"sumtxt\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n32. Number of Japanese databases&nbsp;<span class=\"sumtxt\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n33. Number of Korean databases&nbsp;<br />\r\n34. Number of Non-CJK databases&nbsp;<br />\r\n35. Subtotal Number of databases</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p><b><b><i>Comments and/or Footnotes for 2.2</i></b></b><br />\r\n<strong><u>Include</u></strong><b><b>:</b> </b>paid subscriptions of scholarly journals (unless bundled with print subscription costs, e-journal aggregation service expenditures, expenditures for indexes and abstracts that include substantial access to the ASCII text or full images of serial content, or annual access fees for resources purchased on a &quot;one-time&quot; basis, such as literature collections, etc.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>NOTE: Combine 2.1 and 2.2 data and figures above. Report the total in 2.3.</b></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.3 Electronic Subscriptions Total (2.1 + 2.2)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\">\r\n<p>36. Chinese Electronic Subscription Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(26 + 31) </span>-Number of Databases<br />\r\n37. Japanese Electronic Subscriptions Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(27 + 32) -Number of Databases</span><br />\r\n38. Korean Electronic Subscriptions Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(28 + 33)</span> -Number of Databases<br />\r\n39. Non-CJK Electronic Subscriptions Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(29 + 34) -Number of Databases</span><br />\r\n40. Electronic Subscriptions Total <span class=\"sumtxt\">(30 + 35)</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:110%;\"><b>3. TOTAL Electronic Resource Expenditures <span style=\"color:red;\">(expenditures for 1.4 + 2.3 in U.S. Dollars)</span></b></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"highlight\">Most of the expenditures recorded in these sections should have been included in the Fiscal Support form. Please use the comment field to indicate the portion of electronic resource expenditures not included in the fiscal support form.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span class=\"highlight\"><b><u>Includes</u>:</b> </span></b><span class=\"highlight\">one-time electronic resource purchases and ongoing electronic resource purchases</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"formitemdesc\"><b><strong>41. Grand Total Electronic Resource Expenditures</strong></b> <span class=\"sumtxt\">(expenditures for 20 + 40)</span><b> </b>\r\n\r\n<p><b>&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n<b> </b></div>','sitetext'),(33,'year-pdf-version','CEAL Statistics PDFs - Listed By Year','<h3>CEAL Statistics PDFs (1957-2022/2023)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;<a class=\"btn btn-info\" href=\"https://scho