ns in American Libraries, <strong>1979/1980</strong> (final report).&rdquo; <em>Committee on East Asian Libraries</em> <em>Association for Asian Studies, Inc</em>. 70/71: 68-81.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tsien, Tsuen-Hsuin. &ldquo;Current status of East Asian Collections in American Libraries.&rdquo; <em>Committee on East Asian Libraries</em> <em>Association for Asian Studies, Inc</em>. 50: 47-57. <strong>1975</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&ldquo;Holding of East Asian Libraries in America,.&rdquo;<em>Committee on East Asian Libraries</em> <em>Association for Asian Studies, Inc</em>. 41: 31-35; 42: 22. <strong>1973</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Holding of Far Eastern Materials in American Libraries,.&rdquo;<em> Committee on East Asian Libraries Association for Asian Studies. </em>22: 7. <strong>1967</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Committee on American Library Resources on the Far East, Association of Asian Studies, 1966. <strong>1965 </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;East Asian Collections in America. Present status of East Asian Collections in America,.&rdquo; In <em>Area Studies and the Library</em>, edited by Tsuen-Hsuin Tsien and Howard W. Winger. Chicago and London: University of Chicago Press, 1966: 60-64. <strong>1964</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tsien, Tsuen-Hsun, &quot;East Asian Collections in America.&quot; <em>Library Quarterly, </em>XXXV, No. 4 (1965):260-275. <strong>1964</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nunn G. Raymond, Tsien, Tsuen-Hsuin, &ldquo;Far Eastern Resources in American Libraries.&rdquo; <em>Library Quarterly</em>. V. XXIX No. 1 (1959): 30-31. <strong>1957</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"dcont\">\r\n<p class=\"contact\">Vickie Fu Doll<br />\r\nvdoll [at sign] ku.edu<br />\r\nEast Asian Library<br />\r\nUniversity of Kansas<br />\r\nChair</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"dcont\">\r\n<p class=\"contact\">Wen-ling Liu<br />\r\nwliu&nbsp;[at sign] indiana.edu<br />\r\nEast Asian Library<br />\r\nIndiana University</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','sitetext'),(35,'pdfs-header','CEAL Statistics PDF - Top','<h1>Published Statistics</h1>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-1 pull-right\">\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-info \">\r\n<p>This series report annual statistical data on collections, expenditures, staffing, and user services of East Asian collections in North America libraries. Printed copies of data are published every year in the February issue of <a href=\"http://www.lib.byu.edu/dlib/spc/jeal/\">Journal of East Asian Libraries (JEAL)</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.lib.byu.edu/dlib/spc/jeal/\">JEAL electronic archival issues</a> can be accessed at the <a href=\"http://www.lib.byu.edu/dlib/spc/\">Scholarly Periodicals Center</a> hosted by the Brigham Young University.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"pdfs\">CEAL Statistics PDFs </a>(1999-current)<br />\r\n<a href=\"year-pdf-version\">CEAL Statistics PDFs </a>(1957-2022/2023)<br />\r\n<a href=\"citations\">CEAL Statistics publications citation </a>(The Committee wishes to thank Dr. Tsuen-Hsuin Tsien 錢存訓 for his generous support and permission to use his publications in pdf)</p>','sitetext'),(36,'libraryInformationInstructions','Instructions - Library Information Form +Institutional Structure','<h3 class=\"underline\"><strong>Library Information Form</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:\r\n107%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:black;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;mso-bidi-language:\r\nAR-SA\">This form allows you to update your own library information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Library Name</i></b><br />\r\nLibrary names are in the pull-down list. Use shortened version instead of full name:<br />\r\nEx. <i>Kansas</i> instead of the <i>University of Kansas</i>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Library Type</i></b><br />\r\nChoose from pull-down list:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Canadian university</li>\r\n	<li>Private U.S. university</li>\r\n	<li>State-controlled or public university</li>\r\n	<li>U.S. non-university</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian non-university</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Library Region</i></b><br />\r\nChoose from pull-down list.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New England</li>\r\n	<li>Middle Atlantic</li>\r\n	<li>East North Central</li>\r\n	<li>West North Central</li>\r\n	<li>South Atlantic</li>\r\n	<li>East South Central</li>\r\n	<li>West South Central</li>\r\n	<li>Mountain</li>\r\n	<li>Pacific</li>\r\n	<li>Canada</li>\r\n	<li>Mexico</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Law Library Included (LAW)</i></b><br />\r\nChoose <span style=\"color:blue;\">Yes</span> or <span style=\"color:blue;\">No</span> from pull down list to indicate whether a law library is included in reported data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Medical Library Included (MED)</i></b><br />\r\nChoose <span style=\"color:blue;\">Yes</span> or <span style=\"color:blue;\">No</span> from pull down list to indicate whether a medical library is included in reported data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Submitted by (Name):</i></b> First and last name<br />\r\n<b><i>Position title currently held by the one who submits data:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. Head, Asian Library</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Phone Number (with area code):</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. (234) 123-4567</span><br />\r\n<b><i>E-mail Address:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. user@server.edu</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Fax Number (with area code):</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. (123) 123-6789</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Bibliographic Utilities:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. OCLC, RLG, etc.</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Networks or Consortia:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. Ohiolink, Illinet, GWLA, etc.</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Integrated System Vendor:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. Sirsis, DRA, Ex-Libris-USA, Endeavor, etc.</span><br />\r\n<b><i>OPAC Capability of CJK Display:</i></b><br />\r\nChoose <span style=\"color:blue;\">Yes</span> or <span style=\"color:blue;\">No</span> from pull-down list.<br />\r\n<b><i>Library Homepage:</i></b> <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. http://www.server.edu</span><br />\r\n<b><i>Library Online Catalog:</i></b><br />\r\nURL of your library online catalog: <span style=\"color:blue;\">e.g. http://www.library_catalog.server.edu</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b><mark>Organizational Structure and Operations of Your East Asian Collection (new)</mark>&nbsp;</b></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Full title of East Asian collection _________</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><em><b>Collection Administration</b></em></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Position title in charge of East Asian collection&nbsp; _______</strong></em><br />\r\nTitle of the person in charge of collection/library</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><em>Head of East&nbsp;Asian collection reports to what position title? ______</em></b><br />\r\nThe immediate position title which the head of East&nbsp;Asian collection reports to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Collection organized under what department/unit?&nbsp; ______</strong></em><br />\r\nThe department/unit that&nbsp;is immediately above the collection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>The top hierarchy department/unit the collection is under (if it is different than the previous)&nbsp; ______</strong></em><br />\r\nThe top hierarchy unit which oversees the collection but not the University Library. If it is the University Library, then report that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Except the University&nbsp;Librarian (or the Dean of the Libraries), <u>the title of the next highest position</u>&nbsp;the collection is under&nbsp; ______</strong></em><br />\r\nThe highest position title, except the University Librarian, that oversees the&nbsp;East Asian collection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>The East Asian collection is associated with which&nbsp;other departments/units?______ </strong></em><br />\r\nThe parallel relationship the collection or the person in charge has with other departments/units in the library. Provide those departments/units which the collection has a working relationship with. Examples include the Collection/Content Development, Learning and Research, Technical Processing, Resource Sharing, Faculty Engagement, Digital Humanities, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>East Asian librarian(s) are a part of which of the following group(s)</em></strong><br />\r\n<i>Choose all that apply.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>International/global studies<br />\r\nSubject librarians/consultant group<br />\r\nCollection development<br />\r\nResearch and learning group<br />\r\nTechnical processing group<br />\r\nPublic services group<br />\r\nSpecial collections group<br />\r\nOther </em> (Add&nbsp;additional information in &quot;Notes&quot; box at the end of this form.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><em><strong>Collection Building and Services</strong></em></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Collection Physical Location</strong></em><br />\r\n<em>Choose from pull-down list.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Stand-alone East&nbsp;Asian library/collection building </em><br />\r\n<em>Separate East&nbsp;Asian collection within a library building</em><br />\r\n<em>Separate East&nbsp;Asian collection with some parts interfiled with other collections (by subject, call number blocks, size, etc.)</em><br />\r\n<em>East Asian collection is completely interfiled with the main library collections</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong><label for=\"cealbundle_library_shelvingType\">CJK languages (shelving)</label></strong></em><br />\r\nChoose the shelving method of CJK language materials from pull-down list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Interfiled, no Western language texts<br />\r\nInterfiled, includes Western language texts<br />\r\nCJK shelved separately, no Western language texts<br />\r\nCJK shelved separately, includes Western language texts</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Other______ </em>(Please give additional information in &quot;Notes&quot; box at the end of this form)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Reference/Consultation</strong><br />\r\nOn site<br />\r\nCentralized</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Teaching and Learning</strong><br />\r\nEA by appointment<br />\r\nCentralized</em><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em><strong>Acquisitions (Order and Receiving)</strong></em></strong><br />\r\nSelect all that apply.<br />\r\n<em>On Site<br />\r\nCentralized<br />\r\nOut-sourced</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Cataloging and Processing</strong></em><br />\r\nSelect all that apply<i>.</i><br />\r\n<em>On Site<br />\r\nCentralized<br />\r\nOut-sourced</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Circulation</strong></em><br />\r\nSelect all that apply.<br />\r\n<em>On Site<br />\r\nCentralized</em></p>','sitetext'),(37,'changePasswordInstructions','Instructions - Change Password','<h3><strong><u>Change Password</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure security and prevent unauthorized access, please choose a password that does not relate directly to you. Do not use your first name or birthday. Your password is NOT case sensitive. You can use numbers, English characters, minus sign, and underscore. Do not use spaces and other symbols.</p>','sitetext'),(39,'forgotPassword','Login - Forgot Password text','<h3><strong>CEAL Statistics Database - Forgot Password</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Please enter the primary contact email address, an email will be sent to the primary contact with instructions on resetting the password.</p>','sitetext'),(40,'adminDocumentation','Admin Documentation','<h1 id=\"cealstatisticsonlinedatabase\">CEAL Statistics Online Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#useradministration\">User Adminstration</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#libraryadministration\">Library Administration</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#systemconfiguration\">System Settings</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#textconfiguration\">Text and Files</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note, the above list is not all-encompassing. Most configuration options can be found by clicking on the &quot;Admin&quot; link in the top menu.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2 id=\"useradministration\">User Administration</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"roles\">Roles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are 4 roles a user can have:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Member Institution -\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>All functions in the &quot;Member&quot; menu</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>E-Book/E-Journal Editor\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Add/Edit/Delete E-Books</li>\r\n		<li>Add/Edit Delete E-Journals</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Assistant Admin\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Edit/Enter Surveys (past or present)</li>\r\n		<li>Manage Files</li>\r\n		<li>View Survey Completion</li>\r\n		<li>Text Configuration</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Super Admin\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Full Access to everything in system</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"addinganewuser\">Adding a new user</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Users</li>\r\n	<li>Click the blue button near the top, &quot;Create a new user&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Enter their email, check all the libraries they pertain to, and check the roles you wish to grant them</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"modifyinguserpermissions\">Modifying user permissions</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Users</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the user&#39;s email address in the list of users</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll to the bottom and check the roles you wish to grant or remove from the user</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"addingausertoalibrary\">Adding a user to a library</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Users</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the user&#39;s email address in the list of users</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll down and check the box next to the library(s) you wish the user to be associated with</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"impersonatingauser\">Impersonating a user</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Members&quot; -&gt; Home</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Impersonate -&gt; Select the user from the list</li>\r\n	<li>You are now logged in as that user and can see exactly what they see.</li>\r\n	<li>To return to your administrative account, click &quot;(exit)&quot; in the far upper-right of the screen</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"resetingauserspassword\">Reseting a user&#39;s password</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Ideally the user will reset their own password using the &quot;Forgot Password&quot; link on the Login page. Alternatively, you can go to the login page, click &quot;Forgot Password&quot;, and enter their email address. It will email them their new password (which they can later change in their member screen).</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2 id=\"libraryadministration\">Library Administration</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"addingalibrary\">Adding a Library</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as an Administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Libraries</li>\r\n	<li>Click the blue button near the top, &quot;Create a new library&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in as much as the information as you know</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"addinguserstoalibrary\">Adding users to a library</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>See <a href=\"userAdministration.md\">User Administration</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"modifyingalibraryasanadmin\">Modifying a library as an admin</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as an Administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Libraries</li>\r\n	<li>Find the libary you wish to modify in the list and click its name</li>\r\n	<li>Make any desired changes</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"deletingalibrary\">Deleting a Library</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently there is no way to delete a library. This is to protected the integrity of the database. If you do have a library you need deleted, please email KU webservices, Matt Garrett (mattg@ku.edu).</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2 id=\"systemconfiguration\">System Configuration</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"configuringthelatestyeartoshow\">Configuring the latest year to show</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can configure the last year that shows in the select menus (eg, quickview, table, graph views, etc).</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as an Administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Settings</li>\r\n	<li>Change &quot;Latest year to show&quot; to the desired year. Note: this list automatically grows each year.</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"openingupasurveyforagiventimeperiod\">Opening up a survey for a given time period</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can configure when the surveys will be accessible by your member institutions through the admin settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as an Administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Settings</li>\r\n	<li>Change the &quot;Current Collection Year&quot; to the current year (assuming that is what data you are collecting).</li>\r\n	<li>Change the &quot;Open Date&quot; and &quot;Close Date&quot; to the dates you desire</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"addingothercustomfieldoptionsfortheotherholdingssurvey\">Adding other custom field options for the &quot;Other Holdings&quot; survey</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as an Administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Custom Fields for Other Holdings</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Create a new option&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Enter option label</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2 id=\"textconfiguration\">Text Configuration</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"configuringsurveyinstructions\">Configuring survey instructions</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin or an Assistant Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Text Configuration</li>\r\n	<li>Click next to any of the &quot;Instructions - &quot; or &quot;Survey -&quot; items</li>\r\n	<li>Make any changes desired. (use the &quot;source&quot; button to edit HTML if you wish)</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"editingothertextonthesite\">Editing other text on the site</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin or an Assistant Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Text Configuration</li>\r\n	<li>Click next to any of text items listed</li>\r\n	<li>Make any changes desired. (use the &quot;source&quot; button to edit HTML if you wish)</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"editingothertextonthesite\">Adding Files</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin or an Assistant Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Manage Files</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Upload a new file&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Choose file&quot;, browse to the file and click &quot;OK&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Click &quot;Save Changes&quot;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"editingothertextonthesite\">Deleting&nbsp;Files</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin or an Assistant Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Manage Files</li>\r\n	<li>Find the file in the list, click the red &quot;X&quot; button to the right of the file</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"editingothertextonthesite\">Linking to Files</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Login as a Super Admin or an Assistant Admin</li>\r\n	<li>Using the top navigation, click &quot;Admin&quot; -&gt; Manage Files</li>\r\n	<li>Find the file in the list, to the right of the file name you will see its URL.&nbsp; Copy and paste this as the link to the file.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<style type=\"text/css\">hr{border-top: 3px dashed #2C8383;}\r\n</style>','sitetext'),(41,'member_library_block','Member Page - Library block','<h3>My Library information</h3>','sitetext'),(42,'member_survey_block','Member Page - Survey block',NULL,'sitetext'),(44,'member_myreports_block','Member Page - My reports block','<h3>My Reports</h3>','sitetext'),(45,'member_reports_block','Member Page - Member reports block','<h3>Member Reports</h3>','sitetext'),(46,'member_reports_detailed_expl','Member Page - Member reports - detailed view explanation','<p>The detailed views contain original and derived statistical data that is not readily available in the public portion of the website, such as growth rate and median. It is also possible to view data with averaging over a period of time.</p>','sitetext'),(47,'ebook_intro','Survey - Ebook Form - Introductory Paragraph','<h1>E-Book Database by Subscription</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Please check the boxes next to each subscription your library has&nbsp;for each Chinese, Japanese, Korean,&nbsp;and Non-CJK&nbsp;language.<br />\r\nThis list includes purchased perpetual access eBooks and annually subscribed eBook databases.<br />\r\nData in this list is linked to Form 9: Electronic Resources&nbsp;and Form 10: Electronic Books.<br />\r\nIf you subscribe to a subset of one of these collections, click &quot;customize&quot;, and then enter the appropriate counts in each of the fields.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','sitetext'),(48,'ejournal_intro','Survey - Ejournal Form - Introductory Paragraph','<h1>E-Journal Database by Subscription</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please check the boxes next to each subscription your library has, for each language Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and Non-CJK.<br />\r\nData in this list is linked to Form 3: Serial Titles and Form 9: Electronic Resources</strong>.<br />\r\n<strong>If you subscribe to a subset of one of these collections, click &quot;customize&quot;, and then enter the appropriate counts in each of the fields.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','sitetext'),(49,'av_intro','Survey - Audio/Visual Database Form - Introductory Paragraph','<h1>Audio/Visual Database by Subscription</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please check the boxes next to each subscription your library has, for each language Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and Non-CJK.<br />\r\nData in this list is linked to Form 4:&nbsp;Holdings of Other Materials and Form 9: Electronic Resources</strong>.<br />\r\n<strong>If you subscribe to a subset of one of these collections, click &quot;customize&quot;, and then enter the appropriate counts in each of the fields.</strong></p>','sitetext'),(50,'survey_announcement','Survey - Announcement message for all libraries','<p>Council on East Asian Libraries (CEAL) Statistics Online Form Guide <a href=\"https://guides.lib.ku.edu/c.php?g=1162015&amp;p=8482958\">https://guides.lib.ku.edu/CEAL_Stats</a></p>','sitetext'),(51,'admin_ebook_form','Admin - E-Book Database Form Introduction','<h1>E-Book Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: By default the listing shows the most recent count if the members check the box.&nbsp; EG, if its 2019, and the resource has its most recent number of titles from 2017, that number of titles will be used for 2019.&nbsp; However, if there is an entry for 2019 with number of titles, that will be used instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: It is not possible to delete an entry if a member has selected it for their survey.</p>','sitetext'),(52,'admin_ejournal_form','Admin - E-Journal Database Form Introduction','<h1>E-Journal Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: By default the listing shows the most recent count if the members check the box.&nbsp; EG, if its 2019, and the resource has its most recent number of titles from 2017, that number of titles will be used for 2019.&nbsp; However, if there is an entry for 2019 with number of titles, that will be used instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: It is not possible to delete an entry if a member has selected it for their survey.</p>','sitetext'),(53,'admin_av_form','Admin - Audio/Visual Database Form Introduction','<h1>Audio/Visual Database</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: By default the listing shows the most recent count if the members check the box.&nbsp; EG, if its 2019, and the resource has its most recent number of titles from 2017, that number of titles will be used for 2019.&nbsp; However, if there is an entry for 2019 with number of titles, that will be used instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: It is not possible to delete an entry if a member has selected it for their survey.</p>','sitetext'),(77,'library-libraryName','Library Form - libraryName','Library Name','formlabel'),(78,'library-type','Library Form - type','Library type','formlabel'),(79,'library-region','Library Form - region','Library Region','formlabel'),(80,'library-plilaw','Library Form - plilaw','Law','formlabel'),(81,'library-plimed','Library Form - plimed','Medical','formlabel'),(82,'library-plisubmitterFirstName','Library Form - plisubmitterFirstName','Submitted by: First Name','formlabel'),(83,'library-plisubmitterLastName','Library Form - plisubmitterLastName','Submitted by: Last Name','formlabel'),(84,'library-plipositionTitle','Library Form - plipositionTitle','Title','formlabel'),(85,'library-pliworkPhone','Library Form - pliworkPhone','Phone','formlabel'),(86,'library-plieMail','Library Form - plieMail','Email','formlabel'),(87,'library-plifaxNumber','Library Form - plifaxNumber','Fax','formlabel'),(88,'library-plibibliographic','Library Form - plibibliographic','Bibliographic Utilities','formlabel'),(89,'library-pliconsortia','Library Form - pliconsortia','Networks or Consortia','formlabel'),(90,'library-plisystemVendor','Library Form - plisystemVendor','Integrated System Vendor','formlabel'),(91,'library-pliopac','Library Form - pliopac','OPAC Capability of CJK Display	','formlabel'),(92,'library-plihomePage','Library Form - plihomePage','Library HomePage','formlabel'),(93,'library-plionlineCatalog','Library Form - plionlineCatalog','Library Online Catalog','formlabel'),(94,'libr